und a bug – which was also noticed by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/sitemap-category-priority-is-not-changing/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://wordpress.org/support/topic/sitemap-category-priority-is-not-changing/</a> a couple of years ago.</p>\n<p>It seems the &#8220;Tag pages&#8221; priority and change frequency setting is actually being used for the brand (sitemap-tax-product_brand.xml), product category (sitemap-tax-product_cat.xml) and blog category (sitemap-tax-category.xml) files!</p>\n<p>Instead of these product_brand and product_category XML&#8217;s priority and change frequency being generated by their own respective settings.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m wanting a Sitemap Generator to use for a WooCommerce site – with products, categories and brands, in addition to normal pages and posts – but it does NOT seem like this one caters for setting up individual priorities and change frequency settings correctly for the above items.</p>\n<p>Look forward to your reply on this matter.</p>\n<p>Kindly,</p>\n<p>Luke</p>\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"lukekowald\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:18;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n					\n				\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/sitemap-xml-does-not-exist-in-my-root/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"sitemap.xml does not exist in my root\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s